The build fails because the source archive referenced by `Source:` doesn't exist:

```
error: File /home/abuild/rpmbuild/SOURCES/v1.0.0~beta.26.tar.gz: No such file or directory
```

This almost always means a `_service` file in the package directory wasn't run to generate the source archive. Run it first:

```bash
/usr/lib/build/runservices .
```

Then check that `v1.0.0~beta.26.tar.gz` appears in `~/rpmbuild/SOURCES/`. If a `_service` file uses `obs_scm`, you can also replace the service by adding the appropriate hint to the `Source:` line: